		<a name="lunch" id="lunch"></a>
		<h2>Tortilla Soup</h2>
		<img src="images/lunch.jpg" alt="Tortilla Soup"/>
	    <!--- this image can be accessed at <a href="http://www.tastebook.com/recipes/3449666-Chicken-Tortilla-Souphttp://www.tastebook.com/recipes/3449666-Chicken-Tortilla-Soup"--->

		<h2>Ingredients</h2>
		<ul>
		<li>2 boneless skinless chicken breast halves, cubed </li>
        <li>1 medium onion, finely chopped </li>
        <li>1 clove garlic, minced </li>
        <li>3 medium tomatoes, seeded and chopped </li>
        <li>4 cups chicken broth </li>
        <li>1 teaspoon salt </li>
        <li>1/8 teaspoon pepper </li>
        <li>1 mild green chili, seeded and chopped </li>
        <li>2 tablespoons vegetable oil </li>
        <li>4 corn tortillas, cut in half and then into 4 inch strips (or already prepared tortilla strips instead of oil and tortillas) </li>
        <li>shredded Monterey Jack cheese (about 2 tablespoons for each serving)</li>
        <li>2 tablespoons coarsely chopped fresh cilantro</li>
		</ul>
		<h2>Method</h2>
		<ul>
		<li>Mix chicken, onion, garlic, tomatoes, broth, salt, pepper and the chili together in the slow cooker
        <li>Cover and cook on low heat for 8 hours
        <li>Sprinkle a bit of cheese into each serving bowl
        <li>Ladle soup into bowl over cheese
        <li>Top with cilantro and tortilla chips to serve
		</ul>
		
		<a href="#breakfast">Breakfast</a> 
		<a href="#lunch">Lunch</a> <!--Links for each meal-->
		<a href="#dinner">Dinner</a> 
		
		<a name="dinner" id="dinner"></a>
		<h2>Steak and Chips with Lemon Parsley Butter</h2>
		<img src="images/Dinner.jpg" alt="Steak and Chips with Lemon Parsley Butter"/>
		<!--- this image can be accessed at "http://www.redonline.co.uk/food/recipes/steak-and-chips-with-lemon-parsley-butterhttp://www.redonline.co.uk/food/recipes/steak-and-chips-with-lemon-parsley-butter"--->
		<h2>Ingredients</h2>
		<ul>
		<li>20g butter, for frying</li>
        <li>2 tbsp sunflower oil</li> 
        <li>4x 200g beef steaks</li>
        <li>2 tsp black pepper</li>
        <li>1 tsp rock salt</li>

        <li><p>FOR THE CHIPS</p> </li>
        <li>1kg medium-sized King Edward potatoes</li>
        <li>1 litre sunflower oil, for deep frying</li>
        <li>2 tsp black pepper</li>
        <li>1 tsp rock salt</li>

        <li><p>FOR THE PARSELY BUTTER</p> </li>
        <li>100g butter, softened</li>
        <li>100g parsley, finely chopped</li>
        <li>1 small garlic clove, chopped</li>
        <li>Zest of 1 lemon</li>
        <li>5 tsp black pepper</li>
		</ul>
		<h2>Method</h2>
		<ul>
		<li>Mash all the parsley butter ingredients together in a small bowl. Set aside</li>
        <li>Wash and scrub the potatoes. Cut them into thick chips around 1cm thick and rinse in cold water before drying on kitchen paper.</li> 
		<li>Place the chips into a deep saucepan and cover with the cold sunflower oil.</li>
        <li>3 Place the pan on a medium heat and simmer for 10 minutes. </li>
		<li>Increase the heat until large bubbles are visible and fry the chips, stirring occasionally until crispy and golden. Remove the chips from the oil and season.</li> 
        <li>4 Meanwhile, season the steaks and heat a frying pan, adding the oil and butter. Fry the steaks for 1-4 min</li>
		</ul>
		
